    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for mdadm is now available for openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP3.",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "mdadm is a tool for managing Linux Software RAID arrays. It can create, assemble, report on, and monitor arrays. It can also move spares between raid arrays when needed.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nUncontrolled resource consumption in some Intel(R) SSD Tools software before version mdadm-4.2-rc2 may allow a priviledged user to potentially enable denial of service via local access.(CVE-2023-28938)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for mdadm is now available for openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP3.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of medium. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Medium",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
